  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A screening sensitivity exercise was conducted informally across flow-rate and rotational-speed combinations to bound hemolysis index variability; results confirmed that the five selected operating points bracket the worst-case region. This screening was documented in the engineering notebook but is not separately structured as a formal sensitivity analysis node within this package.",
